snippet.textDisplay: Thank you for mentioning which brands offer olive tones. I have fair to medium skin depending on how much I’ve been outside or if I have a spray tan. I’m Mediterranean so I have olive undertones, which makes it so annoying to find a shade that matches me. I appreciate when brands release more shades, because it reads to me that they have spent a lot of time and effort on the undertones for every shade they release. I was so excited to see that fenty has very light shades that still have olive tones, because that’s exactly what I had been needing that no brand had delivered before. Good shade ranges help us all out, so god bless the people of color who work within these brands to bring that to life. I also want to thank you for giving cream products a shoutout, because I honestly love them and I cannot believe it took me this long to give cream products the love they deserve. I especially love the flower beauty glow drops (their liquid blush), but they are pretty sheer so I don’t know how they’d read on darker skin.
